1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper presents a structural attack against the McEliece system, which is a well-known public key cryptosystem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of Wild Goppa codes from a quadratic finite field extension, which is a topic related to coding theory and information theory. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper mentions the polynomial time complexity of the attack, which is a topic related to computational complexity. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a filtration algorithm to reveal the secret algebraic description of the codes, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper may also be relevant to software engineering, as it discusses the implementation and security of a specific cryptosystem.
